I count how many numbers are out of order in the array:
Best case: 5 or fewer out-of-order  almost sorted
Average case: 6 39 out of order  random
Worst case: 40 or more out-of-order mostly reversed
Why This Works
Insertion Sort is fast if the array is almost sorted.
Selection Sort always takes the same time no matter the order.
Algorithm Choice
Best average case: Use Insertion Sort
Worst case: Use Selection Sort
Effect of Input Order
Insertion Sort: Faster for nearly sorted arrays, slower for messy ones.
Selection Sort: Same speed for all arrays.
